Lawyers for Colorado theater shooting suspect James Holmes have changed his plea to not guilty by reason of insanity, and a judge won't decide on whether to allow it until later this month.

Attorney Daniel King made the request in court today, saying that the defense now has a diagnosis for Holmes, though he didn't specify what it was.

The judge said that he finds 'good cause' to allow the change in plea, will not make his decision until May 28 - three days before a new hearing begins.

Holmes had bushy hair and beard at Monday's hearing. He didn't speak at all and entered the courtroom with his eyes downcast.

